because of backwater reductions in stream power. Bars are deposited downstream because flow energy is expended around ob- structions and bends and because the flow expands downstream of constrictions that result from large obstructions. The formation of bars and pools inherent in many gravel chan- nels can, thus, be enhanced and fixed in position by flow structures set up around large obstructions and bends formed of resistant materials.},
